{
  "number": 1758,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1758",
  "title": "\"Load More\" functionality doesn't work when passing in searchState to component using InfiniteHits ",
  "body": "**Setup:**\r\n- An \"All Results\" component that displays limited # of results for various categories\r\n- A \"Show More\" component using `InfiniteHits` widget that displays certain # of results but ideally would add more results after clicking \"Load More\"\r\n\r\n**Desired Behavior**\r\n- \"All Results\" component shows first as you type in a query and each category section of results has a \"Show more\" link to bring in the \"Show More\" component.\r\n- We want to preserve the current query and show the same results as displayed on \"All Results\" component and as you click \"Load More\", more results would get added on.\r\n\r\nIf I don't pass in the current `searchState` prop to the \"Show more\" results component, the Load More works just fine, but the current query isn't present.\r\n\r\nWhen I do pass it in, the current query is preserved and the same results show, but the Load More stops working (is not disabled).\r\n\r\nIn the end, passing `searchState` that has a non-empty `query` to the `InstantSearch` wrapping `InfiniteHits`, seems to break the Load More functionality and it's not very obvious why, at least to me. Unsure if I'm missing something or if there's a better way of doing this, but let me know if anyone has any ideas.\r\n\r\n**Update:**\r\n\r\nAfter some debugging, I located part of thethe issue which was within `connectInfiniteHits` in the `refine` function. Basically the `searchState` I pass in with the current query `{query: \"some text\"}`  overwrites the `searchState` that is generated somewhere else and passed into `refine`. This loses the `page` key-value from the internally generated `searchState` and thus continues to reset to page 1 since `page` isn't found in `searchState`.\r\n\r\nNeed to do some more digging as to where the `searchState` for `refine` is getting passed in from, but wherever it is, it should just merge in the `searchState` prop that we pass into `InstantSearch` instead of having it completely replaced.",
